Key Match Events: Ajdin Hrustic scored the opening goal in the 29th minute with a deflected long-range strike.
Kusini Yengi added the second goal in the 62nd minute with a header from a Jordy Bos cross.
Nestory Irankunda made his debut for Australia.
Daniel Arzani replaced Irankunda in the 64th minute and showed exciting flashes.
Pre-Game Insights: Nestory Irankunda was handed a shock start by Graham Arnold in an attacking starting line-up.
The match was effectively a dead rubber as Australia had already progressed to the next round of qualifying and claimed top spot in Group I.
Post-Match Reflections: Graham Arnold's team was frustrated with a 2-0 win, as they expected more goals.
The Socceroos' performance was marred by poor crosses and finishing in difficult conditions.
Jordy Bos was highlighted as Australia's main creative outlet and possibly the player of the match.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played in hot, humid conditions on a shabby, waterlogged pitch at the Bashundhara Kings Arena.
Bangladesh managed a shot through Rakib Hossain in the 33rd minute, which was so far off target it ended up in the car park.
A pitch invader caused a stoppage during the match.
